{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xds4XFJusFCtyCkLfmFNrd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current state:\n- The existing 3 nodes have `node.attr.tier: hot` \n- The existing StatefulSet uses the `es-config` ConfigMap\n- The `app-data` index has 3 primary shards + 1 replica each (6 total)\n- I need to add 2 new data nodes with a different allocation attribute (e.g., `tier: warm`)\n- I need shards to relocate to the new nodes\n\nThe plan:\n1. Create a new ConfigMap for the new nodes with `node.attr.tier: warm` and `node.roles: [data]` (no master)\n2. Create a second StatefulSet with 2 replicas using that ConfigMap, and set up service discovery so the new nodes can join the cluster\n3. Then configure the `app-data` index with a routing policy to move shards to the warm tier nodes\n\nActually, I need to clarify the goal here—I'm aiming for 5 total nodes where the new 2 have different attributes and can receive the app-data shards. I need to set up shard allocation rules so the app-data index shards move to the warm nodes. I can use `index.routing.allocation.require.tier: warm` to force all shards there, or `include.tier: warm` to allow them. Since the goal is to get shards onto the new nodes, requiring the warm tier makes sense—and with 3 shards and replica count of 1, the 6 total shard copies can fit across 2 nodes without violating the constraint that primaries and replicas can't be on the same node. With `include.tier: warm`, the node's tier attribute must be warm, so shards would only land on the 2 warm nodes. Given 3 shards with 1 replica each, I need to verify if that's even feasible with the primary-replica constraint. With 2 nodes and 3 shards each having 1 replica, I can distribute all 6 copies across them, so the cluster should reach green status. Now I'm shifting to the implementation approach—I need to create a new StatefulSet for the warm nodes with its own headless service for stable DNS naming, while the discovery can still point to the existing master nodes. I'm planning to set up a ConfigMap for warm node configuration with the tier attribute, then create the headless service and StatefulSet.\n\nWriting the manifests...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":731,"cache_read_input_tokens":32829,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":731},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ff7ae63-23af-4739-8e74-c801ef996d0b","uuid":"0e6e51bc-3e3e-4dea-b76e-560714246039","request_id":"req_011CcLFiumK5TqUH4D6p9Wy7"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Xds4XFJusFCtyCkLfmFNrd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. The existing 3 nodes have `node.attr.tier: hot`. I'll:\n1. Create a ConfigMap for warm-tier data nodes\n2. Create a headless Service for the new StatefulSet\n3. Create a 2-replica StatefulSet `es-data-warm` (data-only, no master)\n4. Set `app-data` index routing to include warm-tier nodes"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":731,"cache_read_input_tokens":32829,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":731},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ff7ae63-23af-4739-8e74-c801ef996d0b","uuid":"aaa82b79-442d-4c6d-b651-34494175f44b","request_id":"req_011CcLFiumK5TqUH4D6p9Wy7"}
