{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0157fpqcXThCpiTwBuKev7i9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 5 nodes are in the cluster:\n- es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2: tier=hot\n- es-data-warm-0, es-data-warm-1: tier=warm\n\nNow I need to configure the `app-data` index to route shards to the warm-tier nodes. I'll use `index.routing.allocation.require.tier: warm` to force all shards to the warm nodes.\n\nWait, but the verification says \"app-data shards are present on nodes outside the original 3\" - which means at least some shards need to be on the new nodes, not necessarily all. \n\nI should use `require.tier: warm` to force all shards onto the warm nodes, which will trigger ES to relocate them from the hot nodes. With 2 warm nodes and 3 shards plus 1 replica, that's 6 total shard copies to distribute, so I need to verify this fits properly.\n\nSince primary and replica of the same shard can't coexist on the same node, I can alternate them across the two warm nodes—P0 and R0 on separate nodes, P1 and R1 on separate nodes, P2 and R2 on separate nodes—which means all 6 copies fit. Now I'll apply the routing filter.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":644,"cache_read_input_tokens":37459,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":644},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1ff7ae63-23af-4739-8e74-c801ef996d0b","uuid":"936926b4-cc6c-4421-a9e9-d11bdad24828","request_id":"req_011CcLFu3Yf2waVXUeHrEPM3"}
